node.text: Truett and Shane team up to answer your questions and talk about pipes and tobaccos... and English Premier League

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokingpipes.com on August 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says '* H Î X TRADE 1826 MARK MA'.

node.text:
Since its beginnings in 1826 as a small family tobacco firm in Svendborg, Denmark, Mac Baren has evolved into one of the world's preeminent manufacturers of fine pipe tobacco, maintaining traditional techniques to make over 60% of all pipe tobacco produced globally. From the light Aromatics of the 7 Seas line to the all-natural blends of the HH series, their tobaccos are admired by pipe smokers of all experience levels for their clarity, reliability, and complexity of flavor. Many of the brand’s most popular mixtures are available in loose or bulk packaging as well, offering Mac Baren’s distinctive Danish blending style at an even more accessible price.⠀
⠀
From now until August 24th, experience that tradition firsthand and save 15% on all Mac Baren bulk pipe tobaccos, available from one-ounce to 16-ounce quantities. It's the perfect opportunity to try something new or stock up on old favorites. Explore the line today.⠀
⠀
#smokingpipes #pipesmokingcommunity #pipesmokers #pipesmokersofinstagram #macbaren #pipetobacco

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Smokingpipes.com on August 17, 2021 tagging @petersonpipes.

node.text:
Peterson has offered filtered pipes since 1947, the Irish marque’s signature style of robust shanks and transitions allowing for a seamless crossover between their filtered and non-filtered renditions of the same shape. For the past 24 years, the Dublin Filter line has championed Peterson’s filtered pipe selection, and today we welcome another filtered pipe series to the Irish marque’s lineup: the Army Filter.⠀
⠀
Combining the timeless aesthetic and convenience of Peterson’s Irish Made Army series with 9mm drilling, Army Filter pipes enjoy the rare combination of accommodating a filter while featuring a hand-shaped nickel army mount, allowing the pipe to be disassembled while smoking. On site now, Peterson’s Army Filter series is available in either a dark-stained sandblast or Peterson’s smooth, walnut Heritage finish. Find yours today at Smokingpipes.⠀
⠀

node.text:
Cherished for their heat resistance and flavor-neutral smoking properties, AKB Meerschaum pipes, tampers, and coloring bowls are hand-carved from whole block meerschaum by some of Turkey's most experienced carvers, such as Tekin, Muhsin, Ali, and others, each piece maintaining the original maker's stamp but united under the AKB name. From traditional pipe-chart designs to evocatively detailed Freehands and figural forms, AKB pipes offer superior durability and patination compared to composite meerschaum. Explore the array of AKB pipes on site now.⠀

Led by Massimo Musico since 2002, Musico Pipes have carved out a particular niche in Italian pipe making. While many Italian workshops create bold, hearty shapes of whimsical, neoclassic design, Musico is known for crafting traditional renditions of English classics. The selection on site now reflects that penchant for refined shapes in smooth or sandblasted finishes, while some are adorned with accents of silver, boxwood, or bone. Explore the Musico selection, on site now.⠀

IMP is Turkey's premier pipe workshop, hand crafting pipes from solid-block meerschaum — prized for its flavor-neutral smoking properties and its ability to patinate. Though many other meerschaum carvers often offer figural shapes, IMP's artisans specialize in more reserved, traditional designs, appealing to aficionados of classic, pipe-chart standards. The selection on site now includes those with reverse Calabash engineering, as well as those accented by silver and colorful acrylic stems.⠀

node.text:
Savinelli Autograph pipes hold a special position at the Italian workshop, and for many pipe smokers, Autographs are among the pinnacle of Italian pipe making. The first Autograph pipes were fashioned in the early 1970s, and unlike Savinelli's regular production pieces — which are produced serially across standardized shapes — all Autographs are completely handmade, with each individual pipe carved from aged, extra-extra-grade plateau briar. Throughout the line's 50 year history, only six artisans have crafted Autograph pipes, with carvers Massimo, Domenico, and Emiliano responsible for their current production and continuing their reputation for superlative grain and creatively stunning shaping.⠀
⠀
Today's curated selection of Savinelli Autographs comprises 24 pipes across the workshop's Autograph and Artisan lines. It's an eclectic and exciting array of shapes, unrivaled in grain orientation whether finished smooth or sandblasted, and a number are further elevated by colorful acrylic stems — a recognizable aesthetic across Savinelli's standard series, but rare for the workshop's Autograph pipes. Celebrate these special Savinelli pipes with us, and explore the entire selection on site now.⠀
⠀
